### MiniC Compiler API - Tests HTTP
### Usar con: VSCode REST Client, cURL, Postman, Insomnia, etc.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Verificar estado del compilador
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/status

### 2. Obtener informacion del API
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 3. Ejemplo simple: Retornar solo AST
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = 5; return x; }",
  "mode": "json",
  "optimize": true
}

### 4. Ejemplo simple: Retornar solo assembly
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = 5; return x; }",
  "mode": "asm",
  "optimize": true
}

### 5. Ejemplo: Retornar AST y assembly
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = 5; return x; }",
  "mode": "both",
  "optimize": true
}

### 6. Ejemplo: Fibonacci
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int fib(int n) { if (n <= 1) return n; return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2); } int main() { printf(\"%d\\n\", fib(10)); return 0; }",
  "mode": "both",
  "optimize": true
}

### 7. Ejemplo: Arrays
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int arr[5] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}; int sum = 0; for (int i = 0; i < 5; i = i + 1) { sum = sum + arr[i]; } printf(\"%d\\n\", sum); return 0; }",
  "mode": "both",
  "optimize": false
}

### 8. Ejemplo: Structs
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "struct Point { int x; int y; } int main() { struct Point p; p.x = 10; p.y = 20; printf(\"%d %d\\n\", p.x, p.y); return 0; }",
  "mode": "both"
}

### 9. Ejemplo: Funciones
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; } int main() { int result = add(5, 3); printf(\"%d\\n\", result); return 0; }",
  "mode": "both"
}

### 10. Endpoint alternativo: Solo AST
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile/ast
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { return 0; }",
  "optimize": true
}

### 11. Endpoint alternativo: Solo assembly
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile/asm
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { return 0; }",
  "optimize": true
}

### 12. Prueba con error semantico (variable no definida)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { printf(\"%d\\n\", undefined_var); return 0; }",
  "mode": "both"
}

### 13. Prueba con error sintactico
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = }",
  "mode": "both"
}

### 14. Codigo vacio (debe dar error)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "",
  "mode": "json"
}

### 15. Ejemplo completo: Control de flujo
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = 10; if (x > 5) { printf(\"Mayor\\n\"); } else { printf(\"Menor\\n\"); } while (x > 0) { x = x - 1; } return 0; }",
  "mode": "both",
  "optimize": true
}

### 16. Ejemplo: Punteros
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = 5; int *p = &x; printf(\"%d\\n\", *p); return 0; }",
  "mode": "both"
}

### 17. Ejemplo: Floats
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { double x = 3.14; double y = 2.86; double z = x + y; printf(\"%f\\n\", z); return 0; }",
  "mode": "both"
}

### 18. Prueba de optimizacion: Con -O1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = 5 + 3; int y = 2 * 4; return x + y; }",
  "mode": "asm",
  "optimize": true
}

### 19. Prueba de optimizacion: Sin -O0
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/compile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "code": "int main() { int x = 5 + 3; int y = 2 * 4; return x + y; }",
  "mode": "asm",
  "optimize": false
}
